What American accent do you have?
Your Result: The Midland

"You have a Midland accent" is just another way of saying "you don't have an accent." You probably are from the Midland (Pennsylvania, southern Ohio, southern Indiana, southern Illinois, and Missouri) but then for all we know you could be from Florida or Charleston or one of those big southern cities like Atlanta or Dallas. You have a good voice for TV and radio.

ME! I WAS THE BROTHER FROM ND! IT WAS ME!

It is amazing how wrong it is to have to go a week before you can see your fiance.  I will never know how I lasted 6 weeks straight.  May anyone considering doing anything close to a 6 week trip away from there significant other be flogged with a 3 inch piece of string.

I, for the first time, realized I will be leaving my home, family, friends, job, and congregation.  All because of a girl.  It will never cease to amaze me the power love has.  If you would have asked me two years ago if I would ever leave Jamestown, I would have laughed and quickly shot down the question.  Yet here I find myself packing up some of my things and sending them with Emily...and I could not be happier.  I can't wait to move into our new house.  I guess that's how thing's go sometimes.
Because it will consume everything and everyone around me in One Fell Swoop.
It's really late, and I should have never signed up for this website.
